value.title: In the end, Mike Pence showed both his guts, and class
value.excerpt: The appalling Jan. 6 insurrection at the Capitol also targeted then-Vice President Mike Pence’s life, yet he still rose to the occasion to fulfill his duty with great courage, and he demonstrated class in attending Wednesday’s inauguration of Joe Biden.

value.title: Fox News host Judge Jeanine lobbied Trump during his last few hours in office to pardon her ex-husband. It worked.
value.excerpt: Fox News host Judge Jeanine successfully lobbied former President Donald Trump in an eleventh-hour effort to pardon her ex-husband in the final hours of Trump's presidency, CNN has learned.

value.title: Biden ditches military flags as part of Oval Office makeover
value.excerpt: With new presidents come new White House decorations – especially in the commander-in-chief’s official workplace, the Oval Office.

value.title: Biden to new administration staffers: Be nice to others or 'I will fire you on the spot'
value.excerpt: President Biden warned new members of his administration Wednesday that he’ll fire them “on the spot” if they fail to treat others nicely.

value.title: GOP looks to Biden administration to ‘lower the temperature’ but voice skepticism
value.excerpt: President Biden made a direct appeal to pro-Trump supporters and Republicans across the nation who did not vote for him to become the 46th president of the United States, calling for everyone to "stop the shouting and lower the temperature."

value.title: Ex-Obama adviser calls Trump supporters an ‘issue of Homeland Security’
value.excerpt: An Obama-era national security adviser painted Trump supporters as an “issue of Homeland Security” and called for government and Big Tech to regulate information on social media in a televised interview Wednesday afternoon.

value.title: Trump Departs Vowing,‘We Will Be Back in Some Form’
value.excerpt: Defeated and twice impeached, the 45th president used his farewell remarks before a sparse crowd to brag about his record and wish luck to the incoming administration.

value.title: ‘Are you QAnon?’: One Trump official’s brush with an internet cult gone horribly wrong
value.excerpt: Some believed he was “Q,” the mythical figure behind an intricate and sprawling conspiracy theory. Here Ezra Cohen-Watnick, a senior Trump intelligence official, shares the story of his ordeal for the first time.

value.title: Biden’s inaugural address was ‘heartfelt appeal for unity’: Karl Rove
value.excerpt: Fox News contributor Karl Rove said Wednesday, President Joe Biden’s inaugural address was a “heartfelt appeal for unity.” Biden was sworn in as the 46th president of the United States and called for unity in his inaugural address amid a nation of political divide.

value.title: Biden reversing travel ban for Muslim countries ‘very disappointing’: Chad Wolf
value.excerpt: Former Acting Homeland Security Secretary Chad Wolf argued on Wednesday that President Biden’s intention to revoke Donald Trump's travel bans for majority-Muslim countries is "going to make the American people less safe."

value.title: Biden, Harris partake in Arlington wreath laying ceremony
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris, after being sworn in at the Capitol, traveled to Arlington National Cemetery for a ceremony at the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier.

value.title: Marco Rubio rejects Biden immigration bill, calls it ‘blanket amnesty’
value.excerpt: Sen. Marco Rubio, R-Fla., on Tuesday rejected an immigration proposal by President Biden, describing its call for an 8-year pathway to citizenship for illegal immigrants as a “blanket amnesty.”

value.title: ‘A Total Failure’: The Proud Boys Now Mock Trump
value.excerpt: Members of the far-right group, who were among Donald Trump’s staunchest fans, are calling him “weak,” in a sign of fraying support.

value.title: Sotomayor mispronounces Kamala Harris' name – Twitter reacts
value.excerpt: Supreme Court Justice Sonia Sotomayor on Wednesday botched the pronunciation of Kamala Harris’ name during her swearing-in as the nation’s next Vice President – and the Twittersphere was quick to pounce on the mistake.

value.title: Pelosi says Trump could be 'accessory to murder' in connection with Capitol riot
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said former President Donald Trump could be considered an accessory to murder in connection with this month's deadly riot at the U.S. Capitol.

value.title: 'This is our historic moment of crisis and challenge': Joe Biden calls for unity in first speech as president – live
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has been sworn in as president, bringing an end to four years of Donald Trump’s leadership in Washington

value.title: Donald Trump grants clemency to legendary Las Vegas gambler Billy Walters
value.excerpt: Famed sports gambler Billy Walters was among the 143 people to which outgoing President Donald Trump granted clemency in his final day in office.

value.title: Joe Biden Invokes Lincoln in Plea for Unity, an End to 'Uncivil War'
value.excerpt: Biden asked those who didn't support him as president to give him a chance and urged people to open their souls and show tolerance.

value.title: How the government will 'thoroughly clean and disinfect' White House furniture, door knobs, and light switches after Trump leaves
value.excerpt: The Trump White House has been a hot spot for coronavirus infections. Joe Biden and his team will want to clean up before moving in.

value.title: Pence skips Trump send-off where outgoing president thanks him, attends Biden inauguration
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence attended President-elect Joe Biden's inaugural ceremony on Wednesday after skipping President Trump's farewell address at Joint Base Andrews.

value.title: Kirstie Alley slams Katie Couric over comments about needing to 'deprogram' Donald Trump's supporters
value.excerpt: Kirstie Alley fired back at Katie Couric over comments she made on Bill Maher’s show about the need to “deprogram” Donald Trump's supporters.

value.title: Racism allowed Donald Trump 'free rein to terrorize the American people for four years:' MSNBC analyst
value.excerpt: New York Times editorial board member Mara Gay said Wednesday that President Trump had been allowed to "terrorize the American people for four years" because of racist elements in the country.

value.title: Melania Trump says serving as first lady was 'my greatest honor'
value.excerpt: Melania Trump told a small crowd of supporters Wednesday that it was "my greatest honor" to serve as the first lady.

value.title: Donald Trump pardons, commutes Lil Wayne, Kodak Black sentences prompting reactions from fans and critics
value.excerpt: Donald Trump has issued a pardon and sentence commutation to rappers Lil Wayne and Kodak Black ahead of Joe Biden's inauguration. President Trump issued 73 pardons and 70 sentence commutations early Wednesday as he prepared to leave office.

value.title: Snoop Dogg praises Trump for commuting sentence of Death Row Record co-founder Michael 'Harry O' Harris
value.excerpt: Snoop Dogg praised President Trump in his final hours in office for commuting the sentence of his friend, Death Row Records co-founder Michael "Harry O" Harris.
